(1)
129 New Dorp Lane, north side, at the head of South Railroad Avenue (formerly 6th Street), showing Gillies' Phoenix Hotel. It was owned by M. S. Burbank in 1898. The view is westward.
August 2, 1929
P. L. Sperr
(2)
Another view, looking east across the Staten Island Railroad
tracks from North Railroad Avenue.
August 2, 1929
P. L. Sperr
